convex\nHamiltonians. Part IV concerns stratified problems in $\\R^N$, i.e. problems\nwith discontinuities of any co-dimensions: the main change compared to the\nprevious version is the introduction of a notion of ``weak'' stratified\n(sub)solution. In Part V, we address the case of stratified problems in bounded\nor unbounded domains with state-constraints, allowing very surprising\napplications as well as singular boundary conditions. Finally, in Part VI we\ndescribe some applications to KPP (Kolmogorov-Petrovsky-Piskunov) type problems\nand we discuss possible extensions to problems with jumps and to ``stratified\nnetworks''.Even if we consider this version as being the final one, all\ncomments are welcome!\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Dec 2018 15:34:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 8 Jan 2020 10:40:02 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 20 Oct 2022 06:49:59 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 13 Apr 2023 13:33:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-14"}
